[32m+[m[32mTwo chunking strategies are available, selectable from the sidebar:[m
 [m
 **Parent-Child Chunking (default):**[m
[31m-- Parent chunks: 3000 chars / 500 overlap — broad context for the LLM[m
[31m-- Child chunks: 500 chars / 100 overlap — precise embedding search[m
[31m-- Retrieval searches children, parent context passed to LLM[m
[32m+[m[32m- Parent chunks: 3000 chars with 500 overlap — provides broad context to the LLM[m
[32m+[m[32m- Child chunks: 500 chars with 100 overlap — used for precise embedding similarity search[m
[32m+[m[32m- Retrieval searches children, but the parent chunk is passed to the LLM for generation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Best for: structured documents with clear sections (our KB has project docs with headers)[m
 [m
 **Semantic Chunking:**[m
[31m-- Embedding cosine similarity detects natural topic boundaries[m
[31m-- Variable-length chunks that respect semantic coherence[m
[31m-- Best for unstructured text where fixed-size splitting breaks mid-concept[m
[32m+[m[32m- Uses embedding cosine similarity to detect natural topic boundaries[m
[32m+[m[32m- Buffer size of 1 sentence, percentile-based breakpoint at 95th percentile[m
[32m+[m[32m- Produces variable-length chunks that respect semantic coherence[m
[32m+[m[32m- Best for: unstructured text where fixed-size splitting would break mid-concept[m
 [m
[31m-Both strategies are implemented in `src/ingestion/chunker.py`.[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why both?** Different document types benefit from different strategies. Project overview docs with clear sections work well with parent-child. Dense technical docs with flowing prose work better with semantic chunking. The user can switch strategies and rebuild the KB to compare.[m
